&lt;h3&gt;What do Team Leaders do?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harness the skills of Kiva’s dedicated volunteers through an innovative crowdsourcing model&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide motivation and leadership to team members to keep loans flowing from Lending Partners to the Kiva website&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support a diverse and multicultural community of volunteers located across the globe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Foster a connection between the volunteer community and Kiva headquarters&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act as a first line of support for our editors and translators to keep Kiva’s processes efficient and sustainable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Craft customized updates and develop creative approaches to strengthen team engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain regular email contact with team members to answer basic questions, provide guidance, and solve problems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Promote the use of Kiva’s loan review resources and escalate policy and technical questions to Kiva staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monitor team productivity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help shape the future of the volunteer loan review program at Kiva&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exchange ideas and perspectives with other Team Leaders and Kiva staff in regularly scheduled conference calls&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help develop, document, and share best practices for Team Leaders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Successful candidates will have these essential skills and qualities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proficient in English&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can commit 4-6 hours a week for 13 months, including availability for approximately 3 conference calls per year with fellow Team Leaders and/or Kiva staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Is a strong communicator and supremely organized&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can forge effective working relationships with colleagues they&#39;ve never met; i&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;s comfortable providing feedback and instruction over email&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enjoys working collaboratively in a team environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enjoys establishing and reaching targets, both for themselves and for their team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Has mature judgement and can work with little supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Is comfortable with internet, email, and basic office applications and software, such as word processing and spreadsheets; regularly checks and responds to emails&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is able to abide by calendared appointments and consistently meets deadlines&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location: Anywhere, but can occasionally accommodate conference calls where differing time zones are prioritized&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a remote volunteer opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
